White Bean and Mushroom Gratin
  --Cook's Illustrated
  
1/2 c evoo, divided
10 oz cremini mushrooms, trimmed and sliced 1/"2" thick
3/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pepper, divided
4 - 5 slices country-style bread, cut into 1/2" cubes (5 c)
1/4 c minced fresh parsley, divided
1 c water
1 tbsp ap flour
1 small onion, chopped fine
5 garlic cloves, minced
1 tbsp tomato paste
1 1/2 tsp minced fresh thyme
1/3 c dry sherry
2x15 oz cans great Northern beans (cannellini or navy work as well)
3 carrots, peeled, halved lengthwise, and cut into 3/4" pieces

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 300F. Heat 1/4 c oil in 12" ovensafe skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add mushrooms, salt, and Â¼ teaspoon pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are well browned, 8-12 min. While mushrooms cook, toss bread, 3 tbsp parsley, remaining 1/4 c oil, and remaining 1/4 tsp pepper together in bowl. Set aside. Stir water and flour in second bowl until no lumps of flour remain. Set aside. Reduce heat to medium, add onion to skillet, and continue to cook, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent, 4-6 min. Reduce heat to medium-low; add garlic, tomato paste, and thyme; and cook, stirring constantly, until bottom of skillet is dark brown, 2-3 min. Add sherry and cook, scraping up any fond. Add beans and their liquid, carrots, and flour mixture. Bring to boil over high heat. Off heat, arrange bread mixture over surface in even layer. Transfer skillet to oven and bake for 40 min. (Liquid should have consistency of thin gravy.) 
Leave skillet in oven and turn on broiler. Broil until crumbs are golden brown, 4-7 min. Remove gratin from oven and let stand for 20 min. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tbsp parsley and serve.


